      "source": "Grammar topic: Yes-no questions with 吗\n \n - Structure: Statement + 吗？\n \n - How to use: Add 吗 to the end of a statement to turn it into a yes-no question. The word order does not change. To answer negatively, use 不 before the verb.\n \n - Examples:\n \n +, 他是老师吗？(Tā shì lǎoshī ma?): Is he a teacher?\n (吗 turns the statement 他是老师 into a question.)\n \n +, 她不是老师。(Tā bú shì lǎoshī.): She is not a teacher.\n (不 goes before 是 to make the sentence negative.)\n \n +, 是，她是老师。(Shì, tā shì lǎoshī.): Yes, she is a teacher.\n (A short yes answer can be followed by the full sentence.)",
